    &lt;Title&gt;Cardiology/Ward 304&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Susan&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;What a great hospital!
 I have been a patient here for approx 5 years 
Last month within 20mins of arrival on the ward for surgery  I was seen &amp;amp; prepared for heart ablation by a nurse &amp;amp; also seen by cardiologist who talked through once again the procedure &amp;amp; after care.  The standard of care on this ward &amp;amp; the cardiology  clinic is of the highest standard including lovely staff involved in the cardio conversions.
Within 2 days of coming home at a weekend follow-up appointments &amp;amp; full report had been sent to myself + GP.
a lovely arrythmia nurse called to check how I was doing and talked me through the after effects of procedure &amp;amp; adjusted my medication.
Despite being a very busy ward &amp;amp; caring for some seriously ill patients there was always someone answering the call button within a short time.  
I know of folk in other parts of the country who are waiting months for the surgery &amp;amp; procedures done here.
Thank you QE - you have every reason to be proud of the standards you strive to maintain.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
